<p>Dimensions track what kind of quantity you have. Adding meters to seconds is not just wrong
at runtime - it's a compile-time type error in Measures.</p>

<h3>The Dimension Type</h3>

<p>Every quantity carries its dimension at the type level. Dimensions are represented as
integer exponents of the seven SI base dimensions:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">structure Dimension where
  length      : Int  -- meter (L)
  mass        : Int  -- kilogram (M)
  time        : Int  -- second (T)
  current     : Int  -- ampere (I)
  temperature : Int  -- kelvin (Θ)
  amount      : Int  -- mole (N)
  luminosity  : Int  -- candela (J)</code></pre>

<h3>Common Dimensions</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">-- Named dimension constants
Dimension.Length      -- { length := 1, ... }  (L)
Dimension.Mass        -- { mass := 1, ... }    (M)
Dimension.Time        -- { time := 1, ... }    (T)
Dimension.Velocity    -- { length := 1, time := -1, ... }  (L·T⁻¹)
Dimension.Acceleration -- { length := 1, time := -2, ... } (L·T⁻²)
Dimension.Force       -- { mass := 1, length := 1, time := -2, ... } (M·L·T⁻²)
Dimension.Energy      -- { mass := 1, length := 2, time := -2, ... } (M·L²·T⁻²)</code></pre>

<h3>Dimension Arithmetic</h3>

<p>When you multiply or divide quantities, dimensions combine correctly:</p>

<pre><code class="language-lean">open Measures.Units.SI

-- Velocity = Length / Time
def velocity := (10.0 *: meter) /. (2.0 *: second)
-- velocity : Quantity { length := 1, time := -1, ... }

-- Force = Mass * Acceleration
def force := (5.0 *: kilogram) *. (9.8 *: meterPerSecondSquared)
-- force : Quantity { mass := 1, length := 1, time := -2, ... }

-- Energy = Force * Distance
def energy := force *. (10.0 *: meter)
-- energy : Quantity { mass := 1, length := 2, time := -2, ... }</code></pre>

<h3>Type Safety in Action</h3>

<pre><code class="language-lean">def distance := 100.0 *: meter
def time := 10.0 *: second

-- This compiles: same dimensions
def total := distance + (50.0 *: meter)

-- This is a compile-time error!
-- def bad := distance + time
-- Error: type mismatch, Quantity Dimension.Length vs Quantity Dimension.Time</code></pre>

